text.tspan: Scope of meeting: teambuilding & defining goals
1. Define & Agree on the way of work
(for participants) increase ability to successfully apply for job
create a template project to learn how to work in IT
learn Agile approach to software development
every meeting should result in output
is based on trust & open communication
time to synchronize with the rest of the team
stand-ups because those meetings are done "standing"
so that they are quick (not too long)
feedback is focused on particular thing / behaviour / issue
it is kind to repond to feedback (to give feedback about feedback)
to make sure that feedback is understood
maybe it is good idea to use Technolog1 instead of Technology2
maybe it is not a good idea to call someone after midnight
